Course is designed for students who have previously studied Russian for one semester and reached the level A1.
 
The topics of the course:

   Getting acquainted, telling about yourself,
   Languages and countries,
   Plural of nouns and adjectives,
   Professions,
   Instrumental case - different contexts of usage,
   Let's meet and let's go! Denoting time and place,
   Prepositional and Accusative case in different contexts,
   Buying food and cooking, visiting restaurant,
   Genitive case - different contexts of usage,
   Holidays, choosing a present,
   Dative case in different contexts,
   Adjectives and proverbs - antonyms and comparative degree,
   Telling about the weather,
   Imperfective and perfective verbs - forms and contexts of usage.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall aim of the course is to enlarge the knowledge and to develop skills acquired at the beginner level by providing a basis for coping with different language situations. Reading, listening, writing and conversational skills will be elaborated during the course.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course a student should be able to: - use the acquired vocabulary and grammar structures in everyday situations; - describe his or her everyday activities; - exchange essential information and express an opinion on familiar topics; - understand and use not complicated language in various communicational situations; - write personal letters and messages.
